"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999963381286505, \"rank\": 3.6614925422431415e-06, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Doubly serving as a stop on the Diamond League schedule, the Prefontaine Classic is one of the most prestigious track & field meets of the year, regularly attracting an elite lineup of international talent.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.161881390882067e-14, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson, who won three medals at her first-ever World Championships last year (1st- 100m, 1st- 4x100m gold, 3rd- 200m bronze) headlines a competitive women's 100m featuring two-time reigning Olympic 100m/200m gold medalistElaine Thompson-Herah(Jamaica),three-time world medalistMarie-Jos\\u00e9e Ta Lou(Ivory Coast), and reigning 60m world indoor championJulien Alfred(Saint Lucia).\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1095, \"end\": 1105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999992514797741, \"rank\": 7.247195343355026e-07, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1461, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999997408322423, \"rank\": 2.591589120699243e-07, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's 100m, reigning 60m indoor world championChristian Colemanhighlights an elite field that includesFerdinand Omanyala(Kenya), the national record holder in the event.\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.999994469091978, \"rank\": 5.516443663742928e-06, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's 200m features Tokyo Olympic 200m silver medalist Kenny Bednarek, who set a world lead and meet record at the Doha Diamond League meet earlier this month (19.67).\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9993748483686098, \"rank\": 0.0006255426763068731, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the famed Bowerman Mile, the last two Olympic 1500m gold medalists inJakob Ingebrigtsen(2020 Tokyo) andMatthew Centrowitz(2016 Rio) and the last three 1500m world champions inGeordie Beamish(2024 indoor),Josh Kerr(2023 outdoor) andJake Wightman(2022 outdoor) are all expected to race one another in one of the deepest mile fields ever assembled.\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American mile record holderYared Nuguse, 2024 world indoor 1500m silver and bronze medalistsCole HockerandHobbs Kessler, Australian mile record holderOliver Hoare, and 3000m/3000m steeplechase world record holderLamecha Girma(Ethiopia) are also expected to line up.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2287, \"end\": 2294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\", \"score\": 0.9998131493704047, \"rank\": 0.00018688109771974233, \"text\": \"Kessler\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cosmo_Kramer\"}, {\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9998972139883776, \"rank\": 0.00010278418967317883, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Hoare\", \"score\": 0.9999999997376108, \"rank\": 1.464243325435556e-10, \"text\": \"Hoare\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Hoare\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Hoare\"}, {\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9989566177763224, \"rank\": 0.0010444245236142977, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Olympic 400m hurdles silver medalist and American record holderRai Benjamin, reigning Olympic pole vault gold medalistKatie Moon, and many other stars are expected to compete.\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2515, \"end\": 2523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.9626890439059801, \"rank\": 0.02598743584341909, \"text\": \"Benjamin\